The paper deals with evaluating the usefulness of audio transformations for voice-only question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves crowdsourcing and evaluation, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing the presentation of answers for voice-only interactions, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
